  "text": "The Java ClassLoader delegation chain in OpenJDK implements a parent-first delegation model for class loading. Here is the complete trace:\n\n## 1. ClassLoader.java (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java)\nThis is the foundational class defining the delegation model. The key method is `loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` at line 534, which implements the parent-first delegation pattern:\n- First checks if the class is already loaded using `findLoadedClass(String)` (line 1231)\n- If parent exists, delegates to `parent.loadClass(name, false)` (line 544)\n- If parent is null, calls `findBootstrapClassOrNull(String)` (line 1208) which invokes the native `findBootstrapClass(String)` (line 1215)\n- If still not found, invokes `findClass(String)` to search the class path\n- If resolve is true, calls `resolveClass(c)` to perform linking\n\nThe native methods `findBootstrapClass()` and `findLoadedClass0()` (line 1237) link to HotSpot for native class loading and lookup.\n\n## 2. BuiltinClassLoader.java (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java)\nThis is the base class for the three built-in class loaders. Defined at line 89, it extends `SecureClassLoader`. It overrides `loadClass(String, boolean)` at line 575 and provides an alternative `loadClassOrNull(String, boolean)` method at line 589. This class implements a custom delegation model:\n- Maps class names to package names\n- If the package is in a module, delegates directly to that module's loader\n- Otherwise follows standard delegation to parent\n\n## 3. ClassLoaders.java (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java)\nThis factory class (line 45) creates the three built-in class loaders:\n- `BootClassLoader` (line 131): Extends BuiltinClassLoader, loads bootstrap modules\n- `PlatformClassLoader` (line 146): Extends BuiltinClassLoader, loads platform modules\n- `AppClassLoader` (line 161): Extends BuiltinClassLoader, loads application classes\n\nThese are initialized in the static block with optional archived class loaders for CDS optimization.\n\n## 4. classLoader.cpp (src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp)\nThis C++ file in HotSpot contains the native implementations of class loading, including the implementation for the native methods called from Java's ClassLoader class.\n\n## 5. systemDictionary.hpp (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp)\nThis file defines the `SystemDictionary` class which is the central caching mechanism for loaded classes. Key methods include:\n- `resolve_or_fail(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader, bool throw_error)` (line 92): Resolves a class, throwing an exception if not found\n- `resolve_or_null(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader)` (line 100): Resolves a class, returning null if not found\n- `load_instance_class(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader)` (line 305): Loads an instance class\n- `load_instance_class_impl(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader)` (line 304): Implementation details\n\nSystemDictionary works with ClassLoaderData to maintain one Dictionary per class loader.\n\n## 6. dictionary.hpp (src/hotspot/share/classfile/dictionary.hpp)\nThis file defines the `Dictionary` class, which provides the actual hash table caching mechanism. The Dictionary class extends `CHeapObj<mtClass>` and uses a `ConcurrentHashTable` for thread-safe concurrent access to cached classes.\n\n## Delegation Chain Flow\nThe complete delegation chain works as follows:\n1. Java application calls `ClassLoader.loadClass(name, boolean)`\n2. The standard ClassLoader or BuiltinClassLoader hierarchy processes the request\n3. Parent-first delegation is applied (delegate to parent before searching locally)\n4. If not in parent, call native methods `findBootstrapClass()` or `findLoadedClass0()`\n5. Native methods query HotSpot's SystemDictionary\n6. SystemDictionary uses Dictionary to look up cached classes by ClassLoaderData\n7. If not cached, load the class and store in Dictionary\n8. Class is returned through the chain back to the caller"
}

